Overview

Between the 2020-01-27 and the 2021-07-19 ( a period 540 days) of a total of 81979 cases have been identified, of which 81979 (100.0%) are confirmed cases.

  • In Fulton County, and over this period, the attack rate is of 747.14 (CI 742.24--752.08) per 10 000.

  • Amongst all cases, at least 5289 (6.5%) have been hospitalised, but 32439 (39.6%) still have an unknown status

  • With reports of 1336 deaths due to COVID, the Case Fatality Ratio is of 1.63% (CI 1.55--1.72), with 42233 (51.5%) of cases missing outcome status.
